"title": "8224: dependence",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8224: dependence",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Reliance upon God or upon others. Dependence on God for help with spiritual and physical needs arises out of an awareness of human helplessness, though dependence may be wrongly directed. People may look to others for encouragement and support, but over-dependence is not commended.</p>\n<h2>Dependence arising from a sense of helplessness</h2>\n<h3>Physical helplessness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:6\">PSA 18:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:4-Ps107:6\">PSA 107:4–107:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:6\">PSA 116:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:38\">MRK 4:38</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:25\">MAT 8:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:24\">LUK 8:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:25-Mark5:26\">MRK 5:25–5:26</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:20\">MAT 9:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:43\">LUK 8:43</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual helplessness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:6\">ISA 64:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:17-Mark9:18\">MRK 9:17–9:18</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:14-Matt17:16\">MAT 17:14–17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:38-Luke9:40\">LUK 9:38–9:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:6\">ROM 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:18\">ROM 7:18</a></p>\n<h2>Dependence on God encouraged</h2>\n<h3>God is to be trusted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:16\">HEB 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:31\">EXO 14:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:3\">DEU 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:5\">PSA 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:10\">PSA 9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:7\">PSA 20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:3\">PSA 37:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:5-Prov3:6\">PRO 3:5–3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:7\">NAM 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:4-John15:5\">JHN 15:4–15:5</a></p>\n<h3>God is a refuge</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:1\">PSA 46:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:27\">DEU 33:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:8\">PSA 62:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:1\">PSA 71:1</a></p>\n<h3>God can help those who depend on him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:6\">HEB 13:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:6-Ps118:7\">PSA 118:6–118:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:4-Ps22:5\">PSA 22:4–22:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:18-Ps33:20\">PSA 33:18–33:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:17-Ps94:18\">PSA 94:17–94:18</a></p>\n<h3>God will help those who depend on him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:13\">LUK 11:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:11\">MAT 7:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps121:2-Ps121:4\">PSA 121:2–121:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:18-Ps145:19\">PSA 145:18–145:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:5\">JAS 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of failure to depend on God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:12\">NUM 20:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:32\">DEU 1:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:23\">DEU 9:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:14\">2KI 17:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:6\">PSA 49:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:13\">PSA 49:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:17\">ISA 42:17</a></p>\n<h2>Dependence on God for physical help</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:12\">2CH 20:12</a></strong> <em>Jehoshaphat and the people of Judah.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:14\">2KI 19:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:14\">ISA 37:14</a> <em>Hezekiah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:18\">2CH 13:18</a> <em>the men of Judah</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:11\">2CH 14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:8\">2CH 16:8</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:9-Ps22:10\">PSA 22:9–22:10</a> <em>David</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:27-Matt9:28\">MAT 9:27–9:28</a> <em>two blind men</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:3-John2:5\">JHN 2:3–2:5</a> <em>Mary</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:8-2Cor1:10\">2CO 1:8–1:10</a> <em>Paul</em></p>\n<h2>Dependence on God for spiritual needs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:14-Mark10:15\">MRK 10:14–10:15</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:14\">MAT 19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:16-Luke18:17\">LUK 18:16–18:17</a> <em>Childlike dependence is necessary for those who would enter God's kingdom</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:27\">JHN 3:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:12\">RUT 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:40-Luke23:42\">LUK 23:40–23:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:47-Luke24:49\">LUK 24:47–24:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:4-2Cor3:5\">2CO 3:4–3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Dependence on God expressed in prayer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:2\">PSA 5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:24\">PSA 22:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:13\">PSA 88:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:1\">PSA 102:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:147\">PSA 119:147</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:1-Ps130:2\">PSA 130:1–130:2</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of those crying out in dependence on God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:23\">EXO 2:23</a> <em>the Israelites in Egypt</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:28\">JOB 30:28</a> <em>Job in his suffering</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:19\">ISA 30:19</a> <em>the people of Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:55\">LAM 3:55</a> <em>Jeremiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:2\">JON 2:2</a> <em>Jonah from within the fish</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:13\">LUK 18:13</a> <em>the tax collector in the temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:5\">ACT 12:5</a> <em>the church praying for Peter</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:11\">2CO 1:11</a> <em>the Corinthians praying for Paul</em></p>\n<h2>Misplaced dependence</h2>\n<h3>Dependence on surrounding nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:18\">JER 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:20-2Kgs18:21\">2KI 18:20–18:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:5-Isa36:6\">ISA 36:5–36:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a></p>\n<h3>Dependence on false gods and religions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:4\">PSA 40:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:20\">DEU 31:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:17\">ISA 42:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:8\">COL 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Dependence on human strength and resources</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:5\">JER 17:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:16\">ROM 9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:16-Ps33:17\">PSA 33:16–33:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:8-Ps118:9\">PSA 118:8–118:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:1-Ps127:2\">PSA 127:1–127:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:8-Eph2:9\">EPH 2:8–2:9</a></p>\n<h3>Dependence on sinful behaviour</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:12\">ISA 30:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:4\">ISA 59:4</a></p>\n<h2>The futility of misplaced dependence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:19\">PRO 25:19</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:13\">JER 2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:6-Isa8:8\">ISA 8:6–8:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:3\">ISA 31:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:13-Hos10:14\">HOS 10:13–10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:20\">ACT 12:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:11-1Thess4:12\">1TH 4:11–4:12</a></p>\n<h2>A proper dependence on others is commended</h2>\n<h3>Human help can strengthen</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:2\">GAL 6:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:9-Eccl4:12\">ECC 4:9–4:12</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of a right dependence on others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:3\">LEV 21:3</a> <em>a priest's support for an unmarried sister</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:11\">DEU 15:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:35-Matt25:36\">MAT 25:35–25:36</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam29:6\">1SA 29:6</a> <em>Achish found David to be a reliable soldier</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:2\">ISA 8:2</a> <em>Uriah and Zechariah were reliable witnesses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:2\">2TI 2:2</a> <em>Reliable teachers are a blessing to the church.</em></p>",
